## 1. CesiumJS (v1.135.0)

**Location:** `app/web/libs/cesium/`  
**License:** Apache License 2.0  
**Copyright:** Copyright 2011-2025 CesiumJS Contributors  
**Homepage:** https://cesium.com/cesiumjs/

### Distribution Requirements:
- ✅ Commercial use, modification, and distribution allowed
- ⚠️ Must include copy of Apache 2.0 license
- ⚠️ Must retain copyright and attribution notices
- ⚠️ Modified files must carry prominent change notices

### Included Third-Party Components:
CesiumJS bundles many open-source libraries (MIT, BSD, Apache-2.0, ISC):
- Knockout.js (MIT)
- tween.js (MIT)
- zip.js (BSD-3-Clause)
- earcut (ISC)
- kdbush, rbush (ISC/MIT)
- pako (MIT)
- protobuf (BSD-3-Clause)
- basis_universal (Apache-2.0)
- Draco (Apache-2.0)
- DOMPurify (Apache-2.0 / MPL-2.0)
- meshoptimizer (MIT)
- URI.js (MIT)
- jsep (MIT)
- topojson-client (ISC)
- See `app/web/libs/cesium/LICENSE.md` for full details

### Cesium Ion Token Notice:
⚠️ Using Cesium Ion services (terrain, imagery, geocoding) requires a personal token.  
Do NOT commit your private `Cesium.Ion.defaultAccessToken` to public repositories.  
Users must obtain their own token at https://cesium.com/ion/

