### NASA Media Usage:
NASA imagery is generally in the public domain. Per NASA guidelines:
- NASA material is not protected by copyright unless otherwise noted
- Use should not imply NASA endorsement
- See: https://www.nasa.gov/nasa-brand-center/images-and-media/

### Natural Earth:
- Free vector and raster map data
- Public domain, no attribution required
- See: https://www.naturalearthdata.com/about/terms-of-use/

---

## 4. TLE Data

TLE (Two-Line Element) data included in `InputData/` may be sourced from:
- **CelesTrak** (https://celestrak.org/) - Free for non-commercial use
- **Space-Track** (https://www.space-track.org/) - Requires registration, usage terms apply

⚠️ Before redistributing TLE data:
- Verify you have rights to redistribute
- Consider providing download scripts instead of bundled data
- Check data provider's terms of service

